  "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://techhub.social/@alabut\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>alabut</span></a></span> I haven’t messed around with the tech stack really that much tbh. It’s been on GH pages + Jekyll for as long as I’ve had the site. But messing around with the structure of the site, its design, etc… comes in waves. About every two years I get bored, or inspired, or w/e and I tend to make more grand changes in terms of how the site looks, feels and functions (as you can kinda see here <a href=\"https://shellsharks.com/notes/2024/02/15/shellsharks-a-visual-history\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"invisible\">https://</span><span class=\"ellipsis\">shellsharks.com/notes/2024/02/</span><span class=\"invisible\">15/shellsharks-a-visual-history</span></a>). In between those episodes, I go through heavy writing period and then nothing 😅</p>",
